# midiout clock multiplication (manual lines 204-227, 383). The clock jack takes a
# modular 16th-note clock and multiplies it by 6 to make a 24-PPQN MIDI clock: it
# measures the input period and interpolates five artificial pulses between real
# edges, so there are exactly six MIDI clocks per 16th. The first edge emits one
# pulse only (no period known yet). Edges here are at t=1, t=61, t=121 (period 60
# ms -> interpolated spacing 10 ms): between t=61 and t=121 there are six pulses
# at 61,71,81,91,101,111.
tickrate 1000
x7 1
patch <<<
[midiout]
    clock = I1
    activesensing = 0
>>>
@1 set I1 1
@1 expectmidi trs clock
@2 set I1 0
@2 expectmidi trs none
@61 set I1 1
@61 expectmidi trs clock
@62 set I1 0
@62 expectmidi trs none
@71 expectmidi trs clock
@81 expectmidi trs clock
@91 expectmidi trs clock
@101 expectmidi trs clock
@111 expectmidi trs clock
@112 expectmidi trs none
@121 set I1 1
@121 expectmidi trs clock
